"title": "5916: pessimism",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5916",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A negative and hopeless attitude, resulting either from viewing the world as being without God or from loss of faith in God.</p>\n<h2>The world may appear to be meaningless</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl1:14\">ECC 1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl1:1-Eccl1:11\">ECC 1:1–1:11</a></p>\n<h2>Wisdom may be pointless</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl1:17-Eccl1:18\">ECC 1:17–1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:12-Eccl2:16\">ECC 2:12–2:16</a></p>\n<h2>Pleasures may be empty</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:1\">ECC 2:1</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Work may be in vain</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:17\">ECC 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:18-Eccl2:23\">ECC 2:18–2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:4\">ECC 4:4</a></p>\n<h2>The world may seem corrupt and oppressive</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:1\">ECC 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:2-Eccl4:3\">ECC 4:2–4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:8-Eccl5:9\">ECC 5:8–5:9</a></p>\n<h2>Loneliness can be depressing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:8\">ECC 4:8</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Wealth is no answer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:10\">ECC 5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:11-Eccl5:15\">ECC 5:11–5:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl6:1-Eccl6:6\">ECC 6:1–6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:18-Luke12:20\">LUK 12:18–12:20</a></p>\n<h2>Life is short and often miserable</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl6:12\">ECC 6:12</a></strong> <em>In the OT, before the resurrection hope was fully developed, this life seemed to be all that there was.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:15\">1CH 29:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:6\">JOB 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:7-Job14:12\">JOB 14:7–14:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:18-Job14:22\">JOB 14:18–14:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:13-Job17:16\">JOB 17:13–17:16</a></p>\n<h2>Suffering may lead to pessimism</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:11\">JOB 6:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:26\">JOB 30:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:16-Lam3:18\">LAM 3:16–3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:11\">EZK 37:11</a></p>\n<h2>Suffering may cause a sense of God's rejection</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:18-Job14:19\">JOB 14:18–14:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:5-Job19:13\">JOB 19:5–19:13</a></p>\n<h2>The godless have no grounds for optimism</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:12\">EPH 2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:13-Job8:15\">JOB 8:13–8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:24\">PRO 10:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:7\">PRO 11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:19-Prov24:20\">PRO 24:19–24:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:3\">ISA 19:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:9\">JER 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:26-Matt7:27\">MAT 7:26–7:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:13\">1TH 4:13</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of pessimism</h2>\n<h3>The Israelites on hearing about the strength of the Canaanites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:31-Num13:33\">NUM 13:31–13:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:28\">DEU 1:28</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's enemies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut2:25\">DEU 2:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:9\">JOS 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>Naomi on her return to Israel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:21\">RUT 1:21</a></p>\n<h3>The Israelites threatened by the Philistines</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:11\">1SA 17:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:6-1Sam13:7\">1SA 13:6–13:7</a></p>\n<h3>Elijah at Mount Horeb</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:9-1Kgs19:10\">1KI 19:9–19:10</a></p>\n<h3>The men with leprosy at the gate of Samaria</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:4\">2KI 7:4</a></p>\n<h3>Judah facing the threat from Aram and Israel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:2\">ISA 7:2</a></p>\n<h3>The Philistine cities on seeing Tyre's destruction</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:5\">ZEC 9:5</a></p>\n<h3>Thomas after the resurrection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:24-John20:25\">JHN 20:24–20:25</a></p>\n<h3>Paul's shipboard companions during the storm</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:20\">ACT 27:20</a></p>\n<h2>The antidote to pessimism is faith in God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:5\">PSA 42:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:13-2Cor4:16\">2CO 4:13–4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:10\">ISA 41:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:21-Lam3:24\">LAM 3:21–3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:7-2Cor4:9\">2CO 4:7–4:9</a></p>",
